CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 15, 1962, pg. 18 reads: " Served 31 Years, Still Going! - This was the theme of the salute to Mr. and Mrs. Edward Coles, both of whom have served in official family of Second Baptist Church School for 31 years, she as superintendent of the children's department and he as general superintendent. Among those who shared the festivities are (left to right) the Rev. Russell Jefferson, Jesse Coles, March Conyers, Abraham Lance, Mrs. Williba Johnson, Mrs. Sylvia Coles, Edward Coles, Gilbert Johnson, Mrs. L. Fleming, James A. Bussey and Mrs. Theresa Harrison. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Rev. Russell Jefferson, Jesse Coles, March Conyers, Abraham Lance, Williba Johnson, Sylvia Coles and Edward Coles, guests of honor; Gilbert Johnson, L. Fleming, James A. Bussey, and Theresa Harrison, seated at banquet table in Second Baptist Church, Homestead
